3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 3633, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 3633. A. There is hereby created an incentive rebate
6 program for certain film projects and eligible television series
7 projects filmed or produced in Oklahoma who meet the requirements of
8 this act.
9 B. The rebate program shall be administered by the Oklahoma
10 Department of Commerce and the Oklahoma Tax Commission.
11 C. By October 1 of each year, the Oklahoma Department of
12 Commerce shall submit an annual report to the Speaker of the House
13 of Representatives, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the
14 Chair of the Appropriations and Budget Committee of the House of
15 Representatives, the Chair of the Appropriations Committee of the
16 Senate and the Director of the Legislative Office of Fiscal
17 Transparency detailing the program and incentive rebate payments.
18 D. The Oklahoma Department of Commerce and the Oklahoma Tax
19 Commission may promulgate rules to implement the provisions of this
20 act.
21 E. To be eligible for a rebate payment a production company
22 shall:
23 1. Submit an application and documentation to the Oklahoma
24 Department of Commerce as required by the Department;
HB2374 HFLR Page 6
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. Have filed any Oklahoma tax returns and tax documents
2 required by law;
3 3. Provide evidence that all Oklahoma crew and local vendors
4 have been paid and that there are no pending liens against the
5 production company in this state;
6 4. Provide evidence of financing for production prior to the
7 commencement of principal photography;
8 5. Provide evidence of a certificate of general liability
9 insurance with a minimum coverage of One Million Dollars
10 ($1,000,000.00) and a workers' compensation policy in compliance
11 with law, which shall include coverage of employer's liability; and
12 6. Provide evidence, as required by the Department, that the
13 projects pursuant to this act are completed; and
14 7. The production company, or its payroll service provider,
15 shall withhold Oklahoma income tax at the highest percentage rate
16 found in the withholding statutes, on all payments to loan-out
17 companies for services performed in Oklahoma. The amounts so
18 withheld shall be allocated to the loan-out company's employees
19 based on the payments made to the loan-out company's employees for
20 services performed in Oklahoma. The loan-out company employees
21 performing services in Oklahoma shall be considered taxable and the
22 loan-out company shall be subject to income taxation in the taxable
23 year in which the loan-out company's employees perform services in
24 Oklahoma.
